main event: On June 6, 1968, Mr. J. Smith and Mrs. M. Johnson reported seeing a bright, oval-shaped object hovering in the sky near Davenport, Iowa.
interesting points: The object appeared to be emitting a bright glow and hovered for several minutes before disappearing rapidly.
Mr. Smith and Mrs. Johnson stopped their vehicle and watched the object for about 5 minutes.
The incident was investigated and documented as part of Project Blue Book, the U.S. Air Force's study of unidentified flying objects.
A separate report describes an unidentified aerial object observed by William Davenport on the same date, described as a dark, oval-shaped silhouette approximately 30-40 feet in diameter.
Another report mentions a photograph taken by a resident of Davenport on June 6, 1968, showing a dark, oval-shaped object in the sky.
sighted object: bright, oval-shaped object; dark, oval-shaped silhouette; dark, oval-shaped object in photograph
witnesses: Mr. J. Smith, Mrs. M. Johnson, William Davenport, unnamed resident
